# MARS – environment variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the keys you need.
# The CLI auto-loads .env on startup (python-dotenv, no extra setup).

# ── GitHub Copilot (free with a Copilot subscription) ───────────────────────
#
# Requires a GitHub OAuth token — Personal Access Tokens (ghp_…) do NOT work.
#
# Recommended: install the GitHub CLI and log in once:
#
#   gh auth login
#
# MARS calls `gh auth token` automatically — no .env entry needed.
#
# ── GitHub MCP server (service agent — repos, issues, PRs, files) ────────────
#
# The [github] entry in agents.ini uses GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN.
# Set it to your GitHub OAuth token (from `gh auth token`) or a PAT
# with scopes: repo, read:org, read:user.
#
# Note: this is a separate setting from Copilot auth above — Copilot is
# discovered automatically via `gh auth token`; this one must be set explicitly.
#
# GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN=gho_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Spawn the agent at runtime with:
#   /spawn github
#
# See SETUP.md §5 for binary download instructions.

# ── Anthropic Claude (paid) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# ANTHROPIC_KEY is also accepted.

# ── Ollama (free, local) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# No key needed. Install from https://ollama.com, then:
#   ollama serve
#   ollama pull llama3.2
#
# Start MARS with:
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider ollama --model llama3.2

# ── Mock (offline testing, no key) ──────────────────────────────────────────
#
# python -m mars.cli.main --provider mock

# ── Usage examples ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider copilot
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider anthropic
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider anthropic --model claude-opus-4-7
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider ollama --model llama3.2
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider mock
#
# Or spawn agents inside the CLI:
#   /spawn copilot
#   /spawn anthropic claude-opus-4-7
#   /spawn ollama llama3.2
#   /spawn mock
